President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden will be hosting Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi for an Official State Visit to the United States on June 22, 2023. The visit aims to strengthen the partnership between the two countries and emphasize the close bonds between Americans and Indians. The leaders will focus on enhancing the strategic technology partnership in areas such as defense, clean energy, and space. They will also discuss expanding educational exchanges and people-to-people ties, as well as addressing common challenges like climate change, workforce development, and health security.